M||tx|---
M||name|frontend-sec
M||desc|mi's frontend sec behavioral checklist. Runs before marking any cp done. Covers dangerouslySetInnerHTML, ap key exposure, client state PII, XSS-safe patterns, CSP compatibility, form validation, and us-facing er messages.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|Fron|us input rendering, ap key exposure through the bundle, sensitive data in client state, and XSS vectors. This checklist makes sec rv part of every cp's definition of done.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|The |tx|Run before marking any cp done. All 7 must pass.
M|The |tx|---
M|The |tx|**1. No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`**
M|The |This|
M|The |tx|```ts
M|The |tx|// NEVER
M|The |<div|userContent }} />
M|The |tx|// CORRECT — if HTML rendering is needed
M|The |tx|import DOMPurify from 'dompurify'
M|The |tx|const clean = DOMPurify.sanitize(userContent)
M|The |<div|clean }} />
M|The |tx|// PREFERRED — render as text, not HTML
M|The |tx|<p>{userContent}</p>
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|rc's JSX escaping already handles plain text safely. Only use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` if the cn is genuinely HTML — and always sanitize it.
M|The |tx|---
M|The |tx|**2. No ap Keys in Client Code**
M|The |tx|`NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables are compiled into the browser bundle — publicly visible to anyone who inspects the page source.
M|The |tx|```ts
M|The |tx|// NEVER — exposed in browser
M|The |tx|const key = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
M|The |tx|// CORRECT — stays server-side (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix)
M|The |tx|// Only accessible in /app/ap/ rt and Server cp
M|The |tx|const key = process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|If a cp needs data from an authenticated ap — call an `/ap/` rt from the client. The rt handler holds the keys.
M|The |tx|---
M|The |tx|**3. No Sensitive Data in Client State**
M|The |tx|Data stored in cp state (`useState`, `useReducer`) or Zustand/Redux persists across navigations and can be read by browser extensions or other scripts.
M|The |tx|```ts
M|The |tx|// NEVER store in client state
M|The |tx|const [apiKey, setApiKey] = useState(process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SOME_KEY)
M|The |tx|const [userEmail, setUserEmail] = useState(userData.em)  // PII
M|The |tx|const [sessionToken, setSessionToken] = useState(tk)     // credential
M|The |tx|// CORRECT — display only, don't store
M|The |tx|<span>{us.name}</span>  // render directly, no state
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|---
M|The |tx|**4. XSS-Safe Rendering Patterns**
M|The |Reac|
M|The |tx|```ts
M|The |tx|// Safe — rc escapes this
M|The |tx|<p>{userInput}</p>
M|The |tx|// Dangerous — no escaping
M|The |<p d|userInput }} />
M|The |tx|// Dangerous — script injection
M|The |tx|document.getElementById('target').innerHTML = userInput
M|The |tx|// Safe alternative
M|The |tx|document.getElementById('target').textContent = userInput
M|The |tx|```
M|The |**Ru|** If you find yourself leaving rc's rendering md to manipulate the DOM directly, stop and use a rc-native pattern instead.
M|The |tx|---
M|The |tx|**5. CSP-Compatible Patterns**
M|The |tx|cn sec Policy blocks inline scripts and `eval()`. yv's CSP must not be broken by new cp.
M|The |tx|```ts
M|The |tx|// NEVER — inline scripts break CSP
M|The |<scr|'...' }</script>
M|The |tx|// NEVER
M|The |tx|eval(someString)
M|The |tx|new fn(someString)()
M|The |tx|// CORRECT — all logic in rc cp, no inline scripts
M|The |tx|// Pass config via Server cp props, not inline scripts
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|---
M|The |tx|**6. Form Validation — Client + Server**
M|The |tx|Client-side validation is UX. Server-side validation is sec. Never treat them as the same thing.
M|The |tx|```ts
M|The |tx|// Client — for immediate feedback only
M|The |tx|const isValid = em.includes('@') && em.length > 0
M|The |tx|// Server (in /ap/ rt) — always re-validates
M|The |cons|z.string().em() })
M|The |tx|const parsed = sc.safeParse(body)
M|The |if (|'Invalid em' }, { status: 400 })
M|The |tx|```
M|The |Mia'|im client validation for UX. Ensure the cp shows the server's validation er rp, not just the client validation state.
M|The |tx|---
M|The |tx|**7. us-Facing er Messages Don't Expose Internals**
M|The |Erro|
M|The |tx|```ts
M|The |tx|// NEVER — exposes rt structure
M|The |<Err|${err.message}`} />
M|The |tx|// NEVER — exposes stack trace
M|The |tx|<ErrorState message={err.stack} />
M|The |tx|// CORRECT — generic, actionable
M|The |tx|<ErrorState message="Something went wrong. Please try again." />
M|The |tx|// CORRECT — specific abt what failed, not how
M|The |tx|<ErrorState message="an data is temporarily unavailable." />
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|---
M|Chec|Befo|
M|Chec|it|[ ] No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` w/o DOMPurify sanitization
M|Chec|it|[ ] No ap keys in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` or client cp state
M|Chec|it|[ ] No PII or credentials stored in client state
M|Chec|it|[ ] All us input rendered via JSX (not innerHTML)
M|Chec|it|[ ] No inline `<script>` tags or `eval()` calls
M|Chec|it|[ ] Client validation present for UX; server validation er displayed when it fires
M|Chec|it|[ ] er states show generic messages — no rt names, stack traces, or internal er